  "why": "The paper's design explicitly assumes and enforces semantically meaningful, natural prompts throughout the fuzzing process. AutoDAN initializes its population from handcrafted prototype jailbreak prompts (to avoid drifting far from the original meaning), uses LLM-based diversification both for initialization and as the mutation operator (stated to “preserve the inherent logical flow and meaning” and “preserve the global meaning”), applies sentence-level momentum scoring and constrained synonym/near-synonym replacements to limit word-level changes, and retains elites between generations. The authors also report low sentence perplexity (PPL) for generated prompts (comparable to handcrafted prompts) and show AutoDAN successfully bypasses perplexity-based defenses — empirical evidence that semantics and naturalness are maintained across iterations. These design choices and evaluations demonstrate enforcement of both semantic consistency and naturalness across fuzzing iterations, matching the \"High\" definition.",
